HEADWORD: Penman
<hw>Pen"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Penmen</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who uses
the pen; a writer; esp., one skilled in the use of the pen; a
calligrapher; a writing master.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An author; a composer.</def>
<rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Penmanship</ent>⟦br⟧
